# SumelaOS-managed .gitignore patterns — SINGLE SOURCE for setup + update, both shells.
# One gitignore pattern per line; '#' comments and blank lines are ignored.
# Add a new per-developer / runtime-artifact pattern HERE only: setup.sh (seed),
# update.sh (reconcile on upgrade), and the PowerShell equivalents all read this file,
# so a new entry reaches fresh AND upgraded installs without drift.
.sumela/local.md
.sumela/.memory-sync.log
.sumela/.graph-sync.log
.sumela/.code-chunks-synced
.sumela/.update-check
.sumela/.retrieval-cache.json
.superpowers/
**/scripts/.superpowers/
graphify-out/
qdrant-storage/
.sumela/_migration/
AGENTS.md.bak*
# Re-include Second-Brain artifacts (specs/plans MUST stay tracked): common host
# .gitignores — e.g. the standard VisualStudio/.NET template's `artifacts/` build-output
# pattern — match ANY directory named "artifacts", silently swallowing
# docs/second-brain/artifacts/ so freshly written specs/plans never appear in
# `git status` or the IDE's Changes view. These negations are appended AFTER the host
# patterns (the SumelaOS block sits at the end of .gitignore), so they win.
# NOTE: gitignore cannot re-include below an excluded PARENT — if the host project
# ignores `docs/` itself, the skills' post-save `git check-ignore` guard surfaces it.
!docs/second-brain/artifacts/
!docs/second-brain/artifacts/**
